statements: SELECT * FROM PhishingLogs;
SELECT user_id, ip_address FROM PhishingLogs WHERE phishing_email_id = 123;
SELECT log_id, date_time FROM PhishingLogs ORDER BY date_time DESC;
SELECT user_id, ip_address, date_time FROM PhishingLogs WHERE user_id = 456 ORDER BY date_time ASC;
SELECT COUNT(log_id) AS total_logs FROM PhishingLogs;
SELECT * FROM PhishingLogs WHERE user_id = 10 ORDER BY date_time DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT user_id, ip_address FROM PhishingLogs WHERE log_id > 100 ORDER BY log_id ASC;
SELECT DISTINCT ip_address FROM PhishingLogs WHERE phishing_email_id = 3;
SELECT log_id, user_id, ip_address, date_time FROM PhishingLogs WHERE date_time >= '2022-01-01' AND date_time <= '2022-12-31' ORDER BY date_time DESC;
SELECT user_id, COUNT(log_id) AS total_logs FROM PhishingLogs GROUP BY user_id HAVING COUNT(log_id) > 10;
SELECT id, email_address FROM phishing_emails;
SELECT ip_address, fall_for_phishing FROM phishing_emails WHERE fall_for_phishing = true;
SELECT * FROM ip_addresses ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT DISTINCT email_address FROM phishing_emails;
SELECT ip_address, user_id FROM ip_addresses WHERE user_id = 123;
SELECT * FROM phishing_emails WHERE fall_for_phishing = TRUE;
SELECT email_address, ip_address FROM phishing_emails WHERE id IN (1, 3, 5);
SELECT email_address, ip_address FROM phishing_emails WHERE id BETWEEN 2 AND 4;
SELECT DISTINCT ip_address FROM phishing_emails WHERE fall_for_phishing = FALSE;
SELECT email_address, ip_address FROM phishing_emails INNER JOIN ip_addresses ON phishing_emails.ip_address = ip_addresses.ip_address;
SELECT * FROM phishing_emails;
SELECT email_address, ip_address FROM phishing_emails WHERE id = 1;
SELECT email_address FROM phishing_emails WHERE email_address LIKE '%gmail.com%';
SELECT * FROM phishing_attempts ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT email_id, count(*) AS total_attempts FROM phishing_attempts GROUP BY email_id HAVING total_attempts > 5;
SELECT id, email_address, ip_address FROM phishing_emails WHERE id = 1;
SELECT * FROM phishing_attempts WHERE timestamp > '2022-07-01 00:00:00';
SELECT email_id, COUNT(*) AS attempts_count FROM phishing_attempts GROUP BY email_id HAVING attempts_count > 10;
SELECT p.email_address, e.timestamp, e.success FROM phishing_emails p INNER JOIN phishing_attempts e ON p.id = e.email_id;
SELECT * FROM exploitation_logs ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT * FROM user_info;
SELECT email_address, username FROM user_info WHERE user_id = 1;
SELECT log_description, ip_address FROM exploitation_logs WHERE user_id = 3 ORDER BY log_id DESC;
SELECT email_id, email_subject FROM phishing_emails WHERE phishing_url LIKE '%paypal%';
SELECT action_id, action_date, action_type FROM user_actions WHERE user_id = 4 ORDER BY action_date ASC;
SELECT * FROM user_info WHERE user_id = 1;
SELECT username, email_address FROM user_info WHERE username LIKE 'A%';
SELECT user_id, email_id, action_type FROM user_actions ORDER BY action_date DESC;
SELECT user_id, email_content, phishing_url FROM phishing_emails WHERE phishing_url IS NOT NULL;
SELECT email_id, email_subject, log_description FROM phishing_emails JOIN exploitation_logs ON phishing_emails.email_id = exploitation_logs.email_id;
SELECT * FROM phishing_emails;
SELECT email_id, email_content, sender_email FROM phishing_emails WHERE receiver_email = 'target@example.com';
SELECT url FROM phishing_links WHERE clicked = true ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT email_id, sender_email, receiver_email, timestamp FROM phishing_emails WHERE sender_email = 'malicious.sender@example.com' AND receiver_email = 'target@example.com';
SELECT description FROM exploit_methods WHERE method_name = 'Phishing' OR method_name = 'Malware' ORDER BY method_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM phishing_emails WHERE sender_email = 'example@sender.com';
SELECT email_id, receiver_email, timestamp FROM phishing_emails WHERE timestamp >= '2022-01-01 00:00:00';
SELECT email_id, email_content, sender_email, receiver_email FROM phishing_emails ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT pl.url, pl.clicked, pe.sender_email FROM phishing_links AS pl JOIN phishing_emails AS pe ON pl.email_id = pe.email_id WHERE pl.clicked = TRUE;

SELECT el.log_id, em.method_name, el.success, el.timestamp FROM exploitation_logs AS el JOIN exploit_methods AS em ON el.method_id = em.method_id WHERE el.success = TRUE ORDER BY el.timestamp DESC LIMIT 10;
